Long-short¶

Factor Model¶

  • E, V estimation

$ E = \beta \bar{f} + \gamma_{reg} I_n$

$ V = \beta \Sigma_f \beta' + \Sigma_\varepsilon + \gamma_{reg} I_{n\times n}$

$ \gamma_{reg} = 0.0001, 0.001$

  • calculation:

$ w = V^{-1} E $

$ w_i = \frac{w_i}{\sum_{j=1}^{N}w_j}$

  • weighting adjustment:

$w = b \times w + (1-b) \times \frac{1}{N} \text{ where } b = 0.5, 2/3, 1$

CAPM¶

  • E, V estimation(only ONE factor in f: market excess return)

$ E = \beta \bar{f} + \gamma_{reg} I_n$

$ V = \beta \Sigma_f \beta' + \gamma_{reg} I_{n\times n}$

$ \gamma_{reg} = 0.0001, 0.001$

  • calculation:

$ w = V^{-1} E $

$ w_i = w_i/\sum_{j=1}^{N}w_j$

  • weighting adjustment:

$w = b \times w + (1-b) \times \frac{1}{N} \text{ where } b = 0.5, 2/3$
